<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F0BFF9CFD52FB32FCA5FB2F" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[691,837,1204,1231]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geniporus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFD52FB32FD27FB2F" box="[691,711,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFD34FB33FCA5FB2F" box="[725,837,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">geniporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0BFF9CFF26FB5EFCFFFAF6" blockId="62.[151,1437,664,1483]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral to bathyal species known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F0BFF9CFC2BFB5EFBA5FB12" box="[970,1093,1240,1267]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.93" metricValueMax="3.85" metricValueMin="0.01" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" unit="m" value="193.0" valueMax="385.0" valueMin="1.0">1 to 385 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFB78FB5EFAF7FB12" author="Maul, G. E." box="[1177,1303,1240,1267]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref60801" refString="Maul, G. E. (1976) The fishes taken in bottom trawls by R. V. ' Meteor' during the 1967 seamounts cruises in the Northeast Atlantic. Meteor Forschungsergebnisse. Reihe D - Biologie, 22, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1976">Maul 1976</bibRefCitation>
) on sand or coarse sand, among seagrass or bedrocks (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFD91FB7AFCF3FAF6" author="Kovacic, M." box="[624,787,1276,1303]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="173 - 184" refId="ref57606" refString="Kovacic, M. (1995) Gobius roulei de Buen, 1928 (Pisces, Teleostei, Gobiidae), a fish new to the Adriatic fauna. Natura Croatica, 4, 173 - 184." type="journal article" year="1995">Kovačić 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0BFF9CFF26FAA6FD27FA2B" blockId="62.[151,1437,664,1483]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Geographic distribution Mediterranean, in the Atlantic recorded only in southern 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFBB6FAA6FB56FADB" box="[1111,1206,1312,1338]" name="Portugal" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFB24FAA6FAA5FADA" author="Maul, G. E." box="[1221,1349,1312,1339]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref60801" refString="Maul, G. E. (1976) The fishes taken in bottom trawls by R. V. ' Meteor' during the 1967 seamounts cruises in the Northeast Atlantic. Meteor Forschungsergebnisse. Reihe D - Biologie, 22, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1976">Maul 1976</bibRefCitation>
). It was described from the Balearic Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFDCAFAC2FD28FABF" author="De Buen, F." box="[555,712,1348,1375]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref52940" refString="De Buen, F. (1928) Descripcion de un nuevo Gobius (G. roulei nov. sp.). Notas y Resumenes, Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia, 2, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="1928">de Buen 1928</bibRefCitation>
), and since has been recorded throughout northern Mediterranean from 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFF39FAEEFEDDFA63" box="[216,317,1384,1410]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFE87FAEEFE47FA63" box="[358,423,1384,1410]" name="Malta" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Malta</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFE58FAEEFD11FA63" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J." box="[441,753,1384,1410]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="287 - 296" refId="ref58780" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J. (2019) Twelve new records of gobies and clingfishes (Pisces: Teleostei) significantly increase small benthic fish diversity of Maltese waters. Mediterranean Marine Science, 20, 287 - 296. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 19816" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Schembri 2019</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFCD4FAEEFC66FA63" box="[821,902,1384,1410]" name="Cyprus" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFC76FAEEFB52FA62" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D." box="[919,1202,1384,1411]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="189 - 190" refId="ref58159" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D. (2006) First record of the Roule's goby, Gobius roulei (Gobiidae), in the Levant. Cybium, 30, 189 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2006 - 302 - 013" type="journal article" year="2006">Kovačić &amp; Golani 2006</bibRefCitation>
), including southern 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFF76FA0BFF03FA46" box="[151,227,1421,1447]" name="France" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFF10FA0AFE16FA46" author="Le Bris, S. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[241,502,1420,1447]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refId="ref59765" refString="Le Bris, S. &amp; Louisy, P. (2015) Signalisation de / Record of Gobius roulei, 25 August 2015 (obs. 11 August 2015, photo  760). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2015">Le Bris &amp; Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
), the Ligurian Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFD2CFA0AFC62FA46" author="Liu, H. T. &amp; Ahnelt, H. &amp; Balma, G. A. C. &amp; Delmastro, G. B." box="[717,898,1420,1447]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="253 - 254" refId="ref60509" refString="Liu, H. T., Ahnelt, H., Balma, G. A. C. &amp; Delmastro, G. B. (2009 b) First record of Gobius roulei (Gobiidae) in the Ligurian Sea. Cybium, 33, 253 - 254. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2009 - 333 - 011" type="journal article" year="2009">
Liu 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFD1DFA0BFCCCFA47" box="[764,812,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. 2009b
</bibRefCitation>
), Adriatic Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFBCAFA0AFB2BFA46" author="Kovacic, M." box="[1067,1227,1420,1447]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="173 - 184" refId="ref57606" refString="Kovacic, M. (1995) Gobius roulei de Buen, 1928 (Pisces, Teleostei, Gobiidae), a fish new to the Adriatic fauna. Natura Croatica, 4, 173 - 184." type="journal article" year="1995">Kovačić 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFB37FA0AFA70FA46" author="Lipej, L. &amp; Bonaca, M. O. &amp; Richter, M." box="[1238,1424,1420,1447]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="165" refId="ref60397" refString="Lipej, L., Bonaca, M. O. &amp; Richter, M. (2005) New contributions to the marine coastal fish fauna of Slovenia. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 15 (2), 165." type="journal article" year="2005">
Lipej 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFAF6FA0BFAA7FA47" box="[1303,1351,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
), Aegean Sea and Levant (Bilecenoğlu 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFDDEFA37FD90FA2B" box="[575,624,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. 2014).
</paragraph>
